honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class SystemSettings_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.SystemSettings_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SystemSettings_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the system settings data from the [STX]KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    UMUnit Measure
    ESESC Sequence Enable
    ASSingle Byte Symbol Set
    DSDouble Byte Symbol Set
    NSDisable Symbol Set Value Selection
    MMMenu Mode
    SEStart of Print Emulation
    ILImage Mode
    LSMenu Language
    GDDisplay Mode
    IMInternal Module Size
    SCScalable Font Cache
    LELegacy Emulation
    ECColumn Emulation
    ERRow Emulation
    FHLFault Handling Level
    FHDFault Handling Void Distance
    FHRFault Handling Retry Counts
    FEFont Emulation
    EMInput Mode
    ATEmulations Used For Auto Input Mode
    EDUser Emulation Mode
    RWRetract Delay
    LRLabel Rotation
    LMLabel Store Level
    FBScalable Font Bold
    DCDot Check on Startup
    DDDot Check on schedule
    DHDot Check Schedule
    FAFormat Attribute
    SRSuppress Auto Reset
    BZBeeper State
    HTHost Timeout
    ZTPrinter Sleep Timeout
    BMBack light Mode
    BNBack light Timer
    ZRRadio Status
    PZPower Down Timeout
    RZRF Power Down Timeout
    UDUser Label Mode
    1Startup Script File
    2Run Once Script File
    3Startup Configuration File
    4Top Level Menu
    5Beep Control Duration
    6Beep Control Quantity
    7Beep Now Duration
    8Beep Now Quantity
    10Periodic Script File
    11Periodic Script Time Interval
    12Web URL
    13Save Last Image
    14Enable File Dump
    15Encrypted File Key
    16Encrypted File Algorithm
    17Shut down Temperature Low
    18Shut down Temperature High

    • Constructor Detail

      • SystemSettings_DPL

        public SystemSettings_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
